  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a ceramic tagine over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the minced garlic and grated ginger and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the ground cumin, smoked paprika, ground cinnamon, salt, and black pepper. Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chopped dried apricots and prunes. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.",
    "Add the rinsed and drained red split lentils, low-sodium chicken broth, and red wine. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes, or until the lentils are tender.",
    "Stir in more water if the tagine becomes too thick.",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with fresh parsley or cilantro, if desired.",
    "Let the tagine rest for 10 minutes before serving to allow the flavors to meld together."
  ],
